  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6819.79 sitting just below the massive 6830 gamma wall (83.8B), dealers are likely selling into this strength as they're long gamma in PIN regime. The wall break detection suggests we've just pushed through a key level, but the thick gamma concentration between 6820-6830 should act as strong resistance with dealers providing natural selling pressure. Given the 1-min pullback (-0.4%) after the 5-min rally (+1%), we're seeing classic mean reversion behavior as dealers hedge their long gamma positions.\n\nKey levels: 6830 is the primary resistance where dealer selling intensifies, while a break below 6747 GEX flip would shift dynamics entirely.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect selling pressure to cap upside near 6830 with choppy action in the 6810-6830 range.",
